peasant /ˈpɛzənt/

(peasants) 

1. N-COUNT A peasant is a poor person of low social status who works on the land; used to refer to people who live in countries where farming is still a common way of life. 农民 

例： ...the peasants in the Peruvian highlands. …秘鲁高原地区的农民们。

